HEADWORD: Ricinelaidin
<hw>Ric`in*e*la"i*din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The glycerin salt of ricinelaidic acid, obtained
as a white crystalline waxy substance by treating castor oil with
nitrous acid.</def>⟦br⟧
